<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:49PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Talladega and central Clay Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 349 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waldo, or near Talladega, moving southwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Munford, Waldo, Camp Mac, Chandler Springs, Ironaton and
Gunthertown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
